            "value": "%3Cp%3ELooking%20at%20Colossians%201%3A13-20%2C%20we%20recognize%20that%20Jesus%20Christ%20deserves%20supremacy.%20In%20this%20passage%2C%20Paul%20describes%20the%20awesome%20spiritual%20dimensions%20of%20Christ%20as%20God%20sees%20Him.%20Verse%2015%20speaks%20of%20Him%20as%20the%20%22visible%20image%20of%20the%20invisible%20God.%22%20Then%20in%20verse%2016%2C%20He%20is%20described%20as%20%22the%20one%20through%20whom%20God%20created%20everything%20in%20heaven%20and%20earth.%22%20He%20is%20the%20actual%20Creator%20of%20anything%20that%20has%20ever%20been%20cre-ated-spiritual%20or%20physical.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJesus%20is%20the%20invisible%20force%20that%20binds%20together%20even%20atoms%20and%20molecules.%20Through%20Him%2C%20all%20things%20%22hold%20together%22%20(v.%2017%20NIV).%20He%20is%20the%20Head%20of%20the%20Body%2C%20the%20Church%20(v.%2018)%2C%20and%20He%20was%20the%20first%20to%20rise%20from%20the%20dead%20as%20a%20firstfruit%20of%20all%20believers%20in%20the%20resurrection.%20Verse%2019%20reveals%20that%20all%20the%20fullness%20of%20God%20dwells%20in%20Him%3B%20that%20is%2C%20God's%20character%2C%20energy%2C%20wisdom%2C%20and%20holiness%20are%20all%20contained%20within%20Him.%20Finally%2C%20His%20blood%20shed%20on%20the%20cross%20is%20the%20means%20by%20which%20fallen%20humanity%20is%20restored%20to%20God%20in%20peace%20(v.%2020).%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJesus%20is%20everything%20to%20God%2C%20and%20He%20should%20have%20supremacy%20in%20our%20lives%20as%20well.%20Why%20should%20we%20be%20fascinated%20by%20anyone%20else%3F%20Who%20else%20or%20what%20else%20besides%20Jesus%20matters%3F%20God%20%22has%20rescued%20us%20from%20the%20one%20who%20rules%20in%20the%20kingdom%20of%20darkness%2C%20and%20he%20has%20brought%20us%20into%20the%20Kingdom%20of%20his%20dear%20Son%22%20(Colossians%201%3A13).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
